      "message": "This bizarre pattern of creating the raw pointer then wrapping it in an upcast sk_sp is me weaving through a few constraints:\n- If I create an sk_sp\u003cGrDirectContext\u003e upfront, I get warned that there\u0027s a bug in C++ where it will not be able to use RVO because the return value is sk_sp\u003cGrContext\u003e which isn\u0027t a perfect match.\n- Also, I can\u0027t call `init` on a GrDirectContext because that\u0027s a protected member. Not sure I understand this one precisely but it makes unwelcome sense.",
